          "statement": "A tank initially contains 100 gallons of pure water. Brine with 2 lb/gal of salt enters at 3 gal/min and the well-mixed solution leaves at 3 gal/min. Find the amount of salt $S(t)$ at time $t$.",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              {
                "title": "Set Up the Differential Equation",
                "content": "Rate in: $2 \\times 3 = 6$ lb/min\nRate out: $\\frac{S}{100} \\times 3 = \\frac{3S}{100}$ lb/min\n\n$\\frac{dS}{dt} = 6 - \\frac{3S}{100}$"
              },
              {
                "title": "Solve",
                "content": "$\\frac{dS}{dt} + \\frac{3S}{100} = 6$\n\nIntegrating factor: $\\mu = e^{3t/100}$\n\n$S = 200 + Ce^{-3t/100}$"
              },
              {
                "title": "Apply Initial Condition",
                "content": "$S(0) = 0$: $0 = 200 + C \\Rightarrow C = -200$"
              }
            ],
            "conclusion": "$S(t) = 200(1 - e^{-3t/100})$ pounds"
          }
        }
